data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` code **won't compile** because the overload now takes `Func<ŌĆ”>` instead of `Expression<Func<ŌĆ”>>`.

**Fix** ŌĆö replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No expression tree manipulation needed anymore.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö two changes

**a) Duplicate names are now uniquified.** If `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column (silent data corruption risk), EF 10 appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`). This **will generate a migration** that renames/adds columns.

To keep the old shared-column behavior, pin names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. This also **generates a migration**.

To preserve old names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
